The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 10 September is 309,133 (549.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 September, there were 14,639 new confirmed cases (26.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 August, there were 7,976 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 84% (6663 extra cases).
